<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 7:16AM CDT  by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Warren and
northeastern McDonough Counties through 745 AM CDT...
At 715 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Little Swan Lake, or 15 miles north of Macomb, moving southeast at 25
mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Little Swan Lake around 720 AM CDT.
Avon around 730 AM CDT.
Prairie City around 735 AM CDT.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
